    a?
        Since the metal parts of the car are earthed, and since metal is a conductor, any charge built up due to the rubbing between the sponge pad, which is an insulator, and the car is conducted away and into ground. In contrast, when rubbing the plastic parts, since the plastic is an insulator, charge can freely build up without being conducted away. 
    b.
        i.
            5/1000 = 6000 * charge
            charge = 5/1000/6000
            = 8.3333333333 * 10^{-7}
            ~= 8.33 * 10^(-7) C
            (= 833 nC)
        ii.
            Suspend a plastic rod on a piece of string. Rub the rod in the same direction vigorously and repeatedly with a plastic cloth. Then, bring the sponge pad slowly close to the side of one end of the rod. If the rod moves as a result of proximity to (but not contact with) the sponge pad, then the sponge pad must be charged, as the rod is charged and the movement could only have been a result (ignoring the effects of air, which may be mitigated by only slowly bringing the sponge pad to the rod) of electrostatic forces as a result of the charge.
